Ventral surface. Pro-, meso- and metasternum bronze, with sparse whitish pubescence, sculpture composed of oval cells with central grains. First ventrite bronze in the middle, towards lateral margins blackish, with sparse whitish pubescence. Other ventrites (with exception of anal ventrite) black, with whitish pubescence becoming denser towards lateral margins. Anal ventrite bronze, its lateral margins serrate, apex truncate, with regularly distributed white setae. Anal ventrite inconspicuously convex apically (
Fig. 26
).

Venter of thorax and first ventrite green, rest of the ventrites very dark green. Lateral margins of anal ventrite (
Fig. 27
) finely serrate with truncate apex. Legs green. Fore tibia (
Fig. 18
) on outer margin serrate.All tibiae on inner margins curved, smooth. Generally shape of all the body parts same as in females, no colour variability observed.

Aedeagus (
Fig. 22
) slender, small, weakly sclerotized, 4.54 times as long as wide. Parameres narrow, widest across apices (ratio length to maximum width 2.78), each apex with four conspicuous setae.
